install package 
compare 

solaris:
show package info:
ex:
pkginfo -l  test

cent os, fedora 
yum 
(1) yum install superiotool 
(2) yum search gcc
	search gcc package
(3) yum upgrade kernel.i686
    yum install kernel-devel
(4) yum groupinstall 'Development Tools'
(5) yum whatprovides ld-linux.so.2

debian:
(1) install
ex:
apt-get install gcc
(2)update package info:
apt-get update
(3)search for package
ex:
apt-cache search gcc
(4)edit package source :
modify /etc/apt/sources.list
ex:
deb http://debian.nctu.edu.tw/debian/ stable main contrib non-free
deb http://ftp.tw.debian.org/debian/ etch main contrib non-free 
deb-src http://ftp.tw.debian.org/debian/ etch main contrib non-free 
deb http://security.debian.org/ etch/updates main contrib non-free 
deb-src http://security.debian.org/ etch/updates main contrib non-free

(5)remove 
ex:
dpkg --remove netatalk

solaris: 
(1) System -> Administration -> Package Manager 
ex: 
search gcc, then Install SUNWgcc 
(gcc is installed on /usr/sfw/bin/) 
(2) pkgadd 
ex: 
pkgadd -d gcc-3.3.2-sol10-sparc-local 
package search location: http://pkg.opensolaris.org/release/en/index.shtml 
(3) pkg install gcc-dev
pkg install -v gcc-dev
fetch from web
(4) pkg install sunstudioexpress


